# Low-Poly Components

Each primitive is **one file** in `src/scene/components/`. Station props
compose them; they never import from `props/`.

## File template

```tsx
import { resolvePosition, type PlacementProps } from './types';

const DEFAULTS = { /* geometry + colors */ } as const;

export interface MyThingProps extends PlacementProps {
  color?: string;
}

export function MyThing({ color = DEFAULTS.color, ...placement }: MyThingProps) {
  return (
    <group position={resolvePosition(placement)}>
      <mesh castShadow>
        <boxGeometry args={[…]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial color={color} flatShading roughness={1} />
      </mesh>
    </group>
  );
}
```

## Rules

- **One component per file** — filename matches export (`Tree.tsx` → `Tree`).
- **Export from `index.ts`** — add the component + its `*Props` type to the barrel.
- **`DEFAULTS` at top** — geometry args and default colors live in a `const DEFAULTS`.
- **Customize via props** — expose `color`, `height`, `scale`, `accent`, etc.; never
  hard-code station-specific values inside a primitive.
- **Placement** — extend `PlacementProps` (`x`/`y`/`z` or `position`); use
  `resolvePosition()` for the root `<group>`.
- **Accent glow** — extend `AccentProps` when the piece uses `emissive`.
- **No `useFrame`** in primitives unless the component owns its animation (e.g.
  `GlowingOrb` with `floating`). Keep primitives mostly static meshes.
- **Low-poly** — `flatShading`, low segment counts (4–12), `castShadow` on solids.

## When to extract vs. keep inline

| Extract to `components/` | Keep in `*Props.tsx` |
|------------------------|----------------------|
| Used on 2+ islands | Used once, very station-specific (hero gate arch) |
| Generic shape (tree, pillar, medal) | Layout that only makes sense in one scene |
| Likely reused in future islands | Composed arrangement of many unique meshes |

Use the `create-low-poly-component` skill when adding a new primitive.
